Step 1 — Data Audit Summary
700 rows across 5 segments, 6 products, 6 countries, and ~15 months. No missing values found in key financial columns. Units Sold are stored with dollar formatting ($1,618.50) but contain numeric values — parsed correctly. Negative profits are stored as $(x) parenthetical format — handled. One structural anomaly identified: Enterprise COGS is uniform at exactly $120.00 per unit across all 100 Enterprise rows regardless of which product is sold. This is not a data entry error — it is a systematic pricing/costing logic failure and is the central finding of this analysis.

